#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:8
#: 4bb54a96581a49b5b148950efe338faa
msgid ""
"The qrexec framework consists of a number of processes communicating with"
" each other using a common IPC protocol, described in detail below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:10
#: ba6fe434809947b18d98fcbf66f58f88
msgid ""
"Components residing in the same domain (``qrexec-client-vm`` to ``qrexec-"
"agent``, ``qrexec-client`` to ``qrexec-daemon``) use local sockets as the"
" underlying transport medium. Components in separate domains (``qrexec-"
"daemon`` to ``qrexec-agent``, data channel between ``qrexec-agent(s)``) "
"use vchan links. Because of `vchan limitation <https://github.com/qubesos"
"/qubes-issues/issues/951>`__, it is not possible to establish qrexec "
"connection back to the source domain."
msgstr ""

