#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:135
#: 29276f751bc0477c84e0fd914efcc0bf
msgid "dom0: request execution of ``cmd`` in domX"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:138
#: 59d1b468723546248032ebf31ac158dc
msgid "qrexec internals diagram dom0-vm"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:143
#: 572ec903b7344f7aae8ade0ff846dea7
msgid "**dom0**: ``qrexec-client`` is invoked in **dom0** as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:151
#: b3ada65b8ba848f490fbb523694656c5
msgid ""
"(If ``local_program`` is set, ``qrexec-client`` executes it and uses that"
" childŌĆÖs stdin/stdout in place of its own when exchanging data with "
"``qrexec-agent`` later.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:153
#: 22a14f4465e3482498a4595a72a06b5f
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client`` translates that request into a ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` "
"message sent to ``qrexec-daemon``, with ``connect_domain`` set to 0 "
"(connect to **dom0**) and ``connect_port`` also set to 0 (allocate a "
"port)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:157
#: 461dc75eac9f41679e08a320f1c31413
msgid ""
"**dom0**: ``qrexec-daemon`` allocates a free port (in this case 513), and"
" sends a ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` back to the client with connection "
"parameters (**domX** and 513) and with command field empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:159
#: 6c9cbb27c5ba4995ab8f9cb01ee02b8b
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client`` disconnects from the daemon, starts a vchan server on "
"port 513 and awaits connection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:161
#: a281e8dc05b14a02900d38b87966c364
msgid ""
"Then, ``qrexec-daemon`` passes on the request as ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` "
"message to the ``qrexec-agent`` running in **domX**. In this case, the "
"connection parameters are **dom0** and 513."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:165
#: 2e33c709aa704046bd2f6bd4b2ce70b8
msgid ""
"**domX**: ``qrexec-agent`` receives ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE``, and starts the "
"command (``user:cmd``, or ``cmd`` as user ``user``). If possible, this is"
" actually delegated to a separate server (``qrexec-fork-server``) also "
"running on domX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:167
#: 4770adaddd4d4d728cbe3baae0fb29f6
msgid ""
"After starting the command, ``qrexec-fork-server`` connects to ``qrexec-"
"client`` in **dom0** over the provided vchan port 513."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:171
#: 5ea8e4454d4a4b5c96d1bd889cac36b6
msgid ""
"Data is forwarded between the ``qrexec-client`` in **dom0** and the "
"command executed in **domX** using ``MSG_DATA_STDIN``, "
"``MSG_DATA_STDOUT`` and ``MSG_DATA_STDERR``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:173
#: b60b49def6364d8d809beb6d811fdf50
msgid ""
"Empty messages (with data ``len`` field set to 0 in ``msg_header``) are "
"an EOF marker. Peer receiving such message should close the associated "
"input/output pipe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:175
#: 364c6b7e91ab4ef5ba215bc165734c24
msgid ""
"When ``cmd`` terminates, **domX**ŌĆÖs ``qrexec-fork-server`` sends "
"``MSG_DATA_EXIT_CODE`` header to ``qrexec-client`` followed by the exit "
"code (**int**)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:182
#: f0bdc8594dca4b34a415317b7a39acc6
msgid "domX: request execution of service ``admin.Service`` in dom0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:185
#: beaed4844f17407b962468d70830f654
msgid "qrexec internals diagram vm-dom0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:190
#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:259
#: 39169fbedb6b4c778fab3f1778ff3ce0 d13f9896f5d14110b8a2e5d18f4c27ac
msgid "**domX**: ``qrexec-client-vm`` is invoked as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:198
#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:267
#: 2b450e49f4ef45bdbe7d34341f5fbf9c 31e41e25d80742508dfdb0c502456227
msgid ""
"(If ``local_program`` is set, it will be executed in **domX** and "
"connected to the remote commandŌĆÖs stdin/stdout)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:200
#: e82c7f1559ea47aa993b870d1d5c485b
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client-vm`` connects to ``qrexec-agent`` and requests service "
"execution (``admin.Service``) in **dom0**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:202
#: 19e6de59e9d442e28bf2fd28f959293f
msgid ""
"``qrexec-agent`` assigns an internal identifier to the request. ItŌĆÖs "
"based on a file descriptor of the connected ``qrexec-client-vm``: in this"
" case, ``SOCKET11``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:204
#: a93db60c7bd34d2b8331c3346b5ff8ee
msgid ""
"``qrexec-agent`` forwards the request (``MSG_TRIGGER_SERVICE3``) to its "
"corresponding ``qrexec-daemon`` running in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:208
#: f972d57094db477e871dd88e8c289159
msgid ""
"**dom0**: ``qrexec-daemon`` receives the request and triggers ``qrexec-"
"policy`` program, passing all necessary parameters: source domain "
"**domX**, target domain **dom0**, service ``admin.Service`` and "
"identifier ``SOCKET11``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:210
#: cbbde8837e404b4abba3111968c1caa7
msgid ""
"``qrexec-policy`` evaluates if the RPC should be allowed or denied, "
"possibly also launching a GUI confirmation prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:212
#: 4361c21d23bc4a92bca8bda585d7fc1f
msgid ""
"(If the RPC is denied, it returns with exit code 1, in which case "
"``qrexec-daemon`` sends a ``MSG_SERVICE_REFUSED`` back)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:216
#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:277
#: 0c1db81eae9a4051a398a43cab5bec65 84a1418915b24c8481f74d909a5b2944
msgid ""
"**dom0**: If the RPC is allowed, ``qrexec-policy`` will launch a "
"``qrexec-client`` with the right command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:224
#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:285
#: 486d0bc58f7f48daa1fc16f317415a0c dd92f686f984492ebce5fecb4237f52f
msgid ""
"The ``-c domX,X,SOCKET11`` are parameters indicating how connect back to "
"**domX** and pass its input/output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:226
#: 956a1794caf0471e988c74446f99fd41
msgid ""
"The command parameter describes the RPC call: it contains service name "
"(``admin.Service``), source domain (``domX``) and target description "
"(``name dom0``, could also be e.g.┬Ā``keyword @dispvm``). The target "
"description is important in case the original target wasnŌĆÖt dom0, but the"
" service is executing in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:228
#: d2829826ba7243a3b33252ffe0eb17f2
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client`` connects to a ``qrexec-daemon`` for **domX** and sends "
"a ``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT`` with connection parameters (**dom0**, and port "
"0, indicating a port should be allocated) and request identifier "
"(``SOCKET11``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:230
#: 41625b47776b4c5385b25523b01ca47a
msgid ""
"``qrexec-daemon`` allocates a free port (513) and sends back connection "
"parameters to ``qrexec-client`` (**domX** port 513)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:232
#: 3042639d598e499b9fe8d93933f2ad7f
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client`` starts the command, and tries to connect to **domX** "
"over the provided port 513."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:234
#: dfd428c5acf84070b35babb05405ee54
msgid ""
"Then, ``qrexec-daemon`` forwards the connection request "
"(``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT``) to ``qrexec-agent`` running in **domX**, with "
"the right parameters (**dom0** port 513, request ``SOCKET11``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:238
#: 01e33b22d4064c809c6413b219517d65
msgid ""
"**dom0**: Because the command has the form ``QUBESRPC: ...``, it is "
"started through the ``qubes-rpc-multiplexer`` program with the provided "
"parameters (``admin.Service domX name dom0``). That program finds and "
"executes the necessary script in ``/etc/qubes-rpc/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:240
#: 6a01f8d61af84311bb495e10bb0fec6e
msgid ""
"**domX**: ``qrexec-agent`` receives the ``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT`` and "
"passes the connection parameters back to the connected ``qrexec-client-"
"vm``. It identifies the ``qrexec-client-vm`` by the request identifier "
"(``SOCKET11`` means file descriptor 11)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:242
#: 075c957782ac492aa83787b53c4d758b
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client-vm`` starts a vchan server on 513 and receives a "
"connection from ``qrexec-client``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:246
#: 709d42789e674be1babf704b6bd87559
msgid ""
"Data is forwarded between **dom0** and **domX** as in the previous "
"example (dom0-VM)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:251
#: c7cf6ad0025c4135a04338db531faaeb
msgid "domX: invoke execution of qubes service ``qubes.Service`` in domY"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:254
#: c2746c269bc74c048b37892473d2c0c8
msgid "qrexec internals diagram vm-vm"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:271
#: 00abc6f32d324be4935c6dfafdd1005f
msgid ""
"The request is forwarded as ``MSG_TRIGGER_SERVICE3`` to ``qrexec-daemon``"
" running in **dom0**, then to ``qrexec-policy``, then (if allowed) to "
"``qrexec-client``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:273
#: c798d62ab86a4b20849f0c821e2c67e9
msgid "This is the same as in the previous example (VM-dom0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:287
#: ddfeeabe85d348bdbbfb2dad53b248b4
msgid ""
"The command parameter describes the service call: it contains the "
"username (or ``DEFAULT``), service name (``qubes.Service``) and source "
"domain (``domX``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:289
#: 2254001522bf40c0af374479e75311ce
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client`` will then send a ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` message to "
"``qrexec-daemon`` for **domY**. The message will be with port number 0, "
"requesting port allocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:291
#: fa148d1485984aada7691c06c3f96d8c
msgid ""
"``qrexec-daemon`` for **domY** will allocate a port (513) and send it "
"back. It will also send a ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` to its corresponding "
"agent. (It will also translate ``DEFAULT`` to the configured default "
"username)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:293
#: 834513d8916b4ac897c2afc07638ab1c
msgid ""
"Then, ``qrexec-client`` will also send ``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT`` message to"
" **domX**ŌĆÖs agent, indicating that it should connect to **domY** over "
"port 513."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:295
#: f26a363ce1904352a0c0200d7d08143b
msgid ""
"Having notified both domains about a connection, ``qrexec-client`` now "
"exits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:299
#: b003ad5dc75d47ff939b86701e7e81df
msgid ""
"**domX**: ``qrexec-agent`` receives a ``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT`` with "
"connection parameters (**domY** port 513) and request identifier "
"(``SOCKET11``). It sends the connection parameters back to the right "
"``qrexec-client-vm``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:301
#: a1e8ac871ebb4e3fabe7d80dcf1bed2b
msgid ""
"``qrexec-client-vm`` starts a vchan server on port 513. note that this is"
" different than in the other examples: ``MSG_SERVICE_CONNECT`` means you "
"should start a server, ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` means you should start a "
"client."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:305
#: ab233acbba9c4367b606cc32685a0fef
msgid ""
"**domY**: ``qrexec-agent`` receives a ``MSG_EXEC_CMDLINE`` with the "
"command to execute (``user:QUBESRPC...``) and connection parameters "
"(**domX** port 513)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:307
#: e3dbe7d366424df4af2899700cc4822e
msgid ""
"It forwards the request to ``qrexec-fork-server``, which handles the "
"command and connects to **domX** over the provided port."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:309
#: 6e1021eb2b4c4268865684d528c4ef53
msgid ""
"Because the command is of the form ``QUBESRPC ...``, ``qrexec-fork-"
"server`` starts it using ``qubes-rpc-multiplexer`` program, which finds "
"and executes the necessary script in ``/etc/qubes-rpc/``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:313
#: 5477f3421abb4fabbbfc22225020205f
msgid ""
"After that, the data is passed between **domX** and **domY** as in the "
"previous examples (dom0-VM, VM-dom0)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:318
#: c807564f1694474da2dc8d95e2e47a33
msgid "``qrexec-policy`` implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:321
#: 84e3c2a1cec84957bf79db8b9340589b
msgid ""
"``qrexec-policy`` is a mechanism for evaluating whether an RPC call "
"should be allowed. For introduction, see :ref:`Qubes RPC administration "
"<developer/services/qrexec:qubes rpc administration>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:324
#: aa7f2dcc6bd14455847f57a31db632d5
msgid "``qrexec-policy-daemon``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:327
#: ac108118a8954d10a14107f6884baa97
msgid ""
"This is a service running in dom0. It is called by ``qrexec-daemon`` and "
"is responsible for evaluating the request and possibly launching an "
"action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:329
#: 8dbe15153b8c401ba4e508af575758a7
msgid ""
"The daemon listens on a socket (``/var/run/qubes/policy.sock``). It "
"accepts requests in the format described in `qrexec-policy-daemon.rst "
"<https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-core-qrexec/blob/master/doc/qrexec-"
"policy-daemon.rst>`__ and replies with ``result=allow/deny``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:331
#: a819e7b14bea4d1c9bba33eb10d9a0e0
msgid ""
"A standalone version is called ``qrexec-policy-exec`` and is available as"
" a fallback."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:334
#: ca2d0a62ff4c401f8cb3d3613a47cd64
msgid "``qrexec-policy-agent``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:337
#: 85ffc7a54a4b4edeb70d99b864921d92
msgid ""
"This is a service running in the GuiVM. It is called by ``qrexec-policy-"
"daemon`` in order to display prompts and notifications to the user."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:339
#: 873b3dff18344b2c922dc72371b83024
msgid ""
"It is a :doc:`socket-based Qubes RPC service </developer/services/qrexec-"
"socket-services>`. Requests are in JSON format, and response is simple "
"ASCII."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/services/qrexec-internals.rst:341
#: aaecb8e8b1054bb6bb4488f909e79f76
msgid "There are two endpoints:"
msgstr ""

